# DOCUMENTATION

- Maintain clear README with setup instructions
- Document API interactions, data flows, and complex logic
- Provide docstrings (NumPy style) for Python code
- Use minimal inline comments except for complex logic
- Document permission requirements

## Code Documentation
- Use NumPy style docstrings for all functions and classes
- Document parameters, return values, and exceptions
- Include examples for complex functions
- Document assumptions and limitations
- Keep docstrings up-to-date with code changes

## Project Documentation
- Maintain a comprehensive README
- Document setup and installation procedures
- Include usage examples
- Document configuration options
- Keep documentation in sync with code

## API Documentation
- Document all API endpoints
- Include request and response formats
- Document authentication requirements
- Include example requests and responses
- Document error responses and codes

## Quarto Documentation
Quarto (.qmd) code cells appear as:
```{r}
# code here
```
- Labels sometimes appear as: `#| label:`
- Comments may describe logic between code cells
- Sometimes code outputs (tables, lists) appear beneath code chunks 